args: Is something wrong, Estelle?\nYou look upset.
The ones you're teaching, you mean?
Yes. Day in and day out, they keep\npulling pranksâ€”and they're getting worse.
Kids don't really know where to draw the\nline, do they?
Those children ought to know better!
Between my constant warnings and the\nLoving Hand, you'd think they'd have\nlearned by now.
Maybe I'm just not able to get anything\nacross to them after all.
What was that sound?! Let's go see...
Oh no, oh no! What should we dooo?
What CAN we do? It's EVERYWHERE!
All the ingredients and dishes are all\nmessed up!
We're gonna get in trouble again...
It's not what it looks like, Reverend!\nR-right, everyone?
R-right! Yeah! We were just... Ummm...
I have had it up to here with you!\nYou've gone too far this time!
At least listen to what they have to say,\nEstelle.
You're a preacher, right? That means,\nfirst and foremost, you talk.
So this is where you went... I was really\nworried when you ran off like that.
Okay, if that's what you want.
I'm a preacher. I should have resorted to\nwords before anything else.
There was no way I was ever going to be\nas good of a preacher as my grandmother!
But if you don't believe me,\nwhy not ask them?
Yeah. Everyone helped bake it.\nWe hope you like it...
Daddy always says that presents help\npeople feel better, so...
We just wanted you to feel better.
We tried really hard, but we kinda messed\nup baking it.
Sorry it didn't turn out that w-well...\n*sniffle* Waaaahhh!
See? They know you're doing your best.
You're getting through to them more than\nyou think.
Maybe you're not exactly like your\ngrandmother, but I still think you make a\nfine preacher.
Don't be. It's I who should apologize to\nall of you.
I am so sorry I never realized how hard\nyou all were trying.
Of course not! I am the one at fault.
So, if it's your fault, does that mean...
You were so worried about us,\nit seems only fitting.
All right. But promise us something.\nMe and the kids.
Promise you'll never give up trying to be\nthe best preacherâ€”and teacherâ€”that you\ncan be.
